    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-06T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="475"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.9169/7–644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McLaughlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-06T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 6, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1329. For Department and Crowley and Dodson FEA<note n="99" xml:id="d475fn99"
                        >Raymond I. Dodson, Assistant to the Director, Pan American Branch, Bureau
                        of Areas.</note> from Embassy Wynn and Acton. Department’s 714, July l,<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d475fn1">Not printed.</note> and previous, export control.
                    Bolivia Country Agency today accepted proposed roll-back of Decentralization
                    Plan unconditionally effective July 10. Despatch follows.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McLaughlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
